      <head>Richard Epstein</head>
      <div>
        <p>Pianist and teacher, son of <ref cRef="entity-000210">Julius Epstein</ref>.</p>
        <p>Epstein was taught by his father and Robert Fuchs, began his career in Berlin and
          Dresden, then in London (1904-14), thereafter in New York. In 1906-07 he performed the C.
          P. E. Bach A-minor Keyboard Concerto in Schenker's edition.</p>
        <p>Correspondence from him to Schenker survives as OJ 10/24 (1903-06: 7 items, 2 concert
          programs).</p>
      </div>
